  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed single storey front extensions, in combination with existing additions, by reason of the proposed siting and poor design (including scale, depth, fenestration and crown roof), would fail to form a subordinate, harmonious addition and would require the loss of soft landscaping. It would therefore introduce obtrusive and incongruous development that fails to respect the high quality, traditional and soft, informal character and appearance of this part of the conservation area, nor the prevailing pattern of development of the wider area. The proposal fails to provide a clear and convincing justification for the heritage harm, nor public benefits to outweigh it, contrary to the requirements of NPPF. The development is therefore contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2021) paragraphs 197, 199, 200, 202 and 206,  Policy D3 (D(1) and (11)) and HC 1 C of The  London Plan (2021), Core Policy CS1 of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), Policy DM1 A, DM1 B (a), (b) (c) and DM7 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010) and the adopted Stanmore and Edgware Conservation Areas SPD (December 2013) including appendix 1: Little Common Conservation Area Appraisal and Management Strategy."
  ],
